Source text

Niger is an underdeveloped country that faces several challenges on its path to development. Here are some recommendations that contribute to its development; diversify its economy, Niger should reduce dependence on a single sector, especially oil. Produce diversification into agriculture, manufacturing and other industries to enhance economic stability, invest in infrastructure; improve transportation, energy, and communication infrastructure. This not only facilitates economic activities but also attracts investment and enhances the overall quality of life, invest in education and skill development programs to empower the workforce, enhance agricultural productivity; support small-scale farmers with modern farming techniques, access to markets, and irrigation. Agriculture plays a significant role in Niger’s economy and can contribute to poverty reduction, strengthen governance structures and institutions to ensure transparency and accountability. Effective governance reduces corruption and attracts foreign investments and implement poverty alleviation programs to implement targeted programs to alleviate poverty, focusing on vulnerable populations. Reference:, Francophone Africa Pre &Post-Independence by Professor Victor Ariole & Wikipedia
